// Rule: All filenames must use kebab-case (lowercase letters, numbers, and hyphens only; no underscores or camelCase).
// Example: use `my-component.tsx` instead of `MyComponent.tsx` or `my_component.tsx`.

// Rule: When creating or importing UI components, prefer using shadcn/ui components.
// Example: Use `import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"` (shadcn) instead of other UI libraries or custom button implementations.

// Rule: Follow the established folder structure for organizing code:
// - src/components/: Reusable UI components organized by category
// - src/features/: Feature-based modules with their own components, hooks, and logic
// - src/hooks/: Custom React hooks (use kebab-case: use-auth-state.ts, use-api-call.ts)
// - src/lib/: Utility functions, constants, and type definitions
// - src/services/: API and AWS service integrations
// - src/stores/: State management (Zustand/Redux stores)
// - src/routes/: TanStack Router route definitions (keep existing structure)
// - src/styles/: Global and component-specific styles

// Rule: Feature-based organization - each feature should be self-contained:
// - src/features/auth/ should contain auth-related components, hooks, and logic
// - src/features/dashboard/ should contain dashboard-specific functionality
// - src/features/profile/ should contain profile management code

// Rule: Component organization:
// - src/components/ui/: shadcn/ui components (keep as-is, don't modify)
// - src/components/auth/: Authentication-related components (login-form.tsx, signup-form.tsx)
// - src/components/layout/: Layout components (header.tsx, footer.tsx, sidebar.tsx)
// - src/components/forms/: Reusable form components (form-field.tsx, form-wrapper.tsx)

// Rule: File naming conventions for different types:
// - Components: kebab-case with descriptive names (user-profile-card.tsx, auth-modal.tsx)
// - Hooks: use- prefix with kebab-case (use-aws-auth.ts, use-api-query.ts)
// - Services: kebab-case with service suffix (auth-service.ts, aws-config.ts)
// - Types: kebab-case with type suffix (user-types.ts, api-types.ts)
// - Utils: kebab-case with descriptive names (date-helpers.ts, validation-utils.ts)

// Rule: Import organization - use absolute imports with @/ prefix:
// - Components: import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
// - Features: import { useAuth } from "@/features/auth/use-auth"
// - Hooks: import { useApiCall } from "@/hooks/use-api-call"
// - Services: import { authService } from "@/services/auth-service"
// - Types: import { User } from "@/types/user-types"

// Rule: Keep existing infrastructure files unchanged:
// - amplify/ directory and configuration
// - scripts/ directory and build scripts
// - public/ directory and static assets
// - TanStack Router routes in src/routes/
// - shadcn/ui components in src/components/ui/

// Rule: AWS integration patterns:
// - AWS-specific services go in src/services/aws/
// - Use AWS SDK v3 patterns and best practices
// - Keep AWS configuration in amplify/ directory
// - Implement proper error handling for AWS service calls

// Rule: State management:
// - Use Zustand for simple state management
// - Keep stores in src/stores/ with kebab-case naming
// - Each store should be focused on a specific domain
// - Example: auth-store.ts, user-store.ts, app-store.ts

// Rule: Code splitting and lazy loading
// - Use React.lazy and Suspense for code splitting large components and feature modules.
// - Prefer dynamic imports for route-level and feature-level code splitting.
// - Place code-split components in their appropriate feature or component folder.
// - Example: const Dashboard = React.lazy(() => import("@/features/dashboard/dashboard-page"))
// - Always provide a fallback UI (e.g., loading spinner from shadcn/ui) when using Suspense for lazy-loaded components.
